  "storyline": "# Storyline\n\n## Context\n\nGraduate analytics work at GWU combined academic modeling, assistantship operations, and applied project delivery. The work spanned text analytics, sensor modeling, sports valuation, and technical support workflows.\n\n## Workflow\n\nThe experience moved from raw data collection and cleaning into feature engineering, model development, validation, and visualization. Assistantship work added an operational layer through inventory analysis and LLM-assisted assignment evaluation.\n\n## Technical Implementation\n\n- **Distributed text analytics:** processed large-scale Yelp review data through Spark and Databricks workflows for sentiment analysis.\n- **LLM grading workflow:** supported an auto-grading pipeline using BERT/LLM-assisted evaluation for 400+ assignments.\n- **Biomedical signal modeling:** modeled panic detection from HRV/BP sensor features with Bi-LSTM and cross-validation.\n- **Sports valuation analytics:** mapped player value indicators across FIFA and NBA-style data with PCA, regression, and Dash/Plotly visualization.\n- **Technical systems analysis:** analyzed inventory and usage patterns to identify breakpoints in technical assistant workflows.\n\n## Outcomes\n\nThe work produced a broad applied analytics portfolio across data engineering, ML modeling, visualization, and operational analysis, with measurable scale across 10M+ reviews, 400+ assignments, and 25K+ player records."
